Package: IRS
Title: Iterative Reference Selection for Microbiome Normalization
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: 
    person("Yiming", "Shi", , "yimingshi@wustl.edu", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0001-7525-6471"))
Description: Provides a robust iterative algorithm for selecting reference taxa 
    in microbiome data analysis. It combines Kendall's rank correlation and 
    robust Poisson regression with sandwich variance estimators to identify 
    taxa that are stable across experimental conditions, facilitating 
    bias-reduced normalization.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
